🧠 Deep Dive: Dataset/ Folder Structure & Content developed by Mohammed Rasol Al Saidat April 2025

📂 Folder: Dataset/ Purpose:

This folder houses the raw labeled SMS data that is used to:
1) Train Word2Vec embeddings
2)Build input tensors for the CNN–BiGRU model
3)Evaluate the model via metrics like ROC, accuracy, F1-score, etc.

📄 Core File: smishing_dataset.csv from Archive.zip
Required Columns:
Column Name	Type	Description
text	string	Raw Arabic SMS content
label	int	Target classification label: 1 for smishing (malicious), 0 for legitimate
Example Rows:
text,label
"تهانينا! لقد ربحت 10000 دولار. اضغط هنا لاستلام جائزتك.",1
"مرحبا بك، هذه تذكير بموعدك في المستشفى.",0
"تم تعليق حسابك البنكي، قم بالتحديث الآن.",1
"لا تنس دفع فاتورتك هذا الأسبوع.",0

⚙️ Technical Requirements for This Dataset
1. Text Quality & Format

#Arabic NLP poses unique challenges:

1) Diacritics (تشكيل): Commonly removed in preprocessing to reduce noise

2) Letter Variants: Normalize different forms (e.g., “أ”, “إ”, “آ” → “ا”)

3) Elongations: Remove character elongations (e.g., “مبروووووك” → “مبروك”)

4) Mixed Scripts: Handle Arabic + Latin (e.g., short URLs, numbers)

🔍 The preprocessing.py file is expected to clean, normalize, and tokenize the Arabic text using tools like:

A) FarasaSegmenter (for tokenization)

B) Regex-based cleaning functions

C) NLTK or custom Arabic stemmers/normalizers

2. Class Distribution

It is critical to maintain a balanced dataset:

Smishing messages are often minority class, but you should either Use stratified sampling, Apply oversampling (e.g., SMOTE) or undersampling during training
Use class weights in the loss function.

📊 Ideally:

50% label = 1 (Smishing)

50% label = 0 (Ham/Legitimate)

If not, report class imbalance and handle accordingly in training logic.

3. Data Volume Requirements

For deep learning to generalize well:

Model Type	Minimum Recommended Rows
CNN–BiGRU Hybrid	5,000+ rows
Small Experimental	500–1,000 rows
Word2Vec Training	10,000+ raw sentences

🧠 Note: Even if you have 2,000–3,000 samples, the model can learn patterns, but the risk of overfitting increases — apply dropout, early stopping, or k-fold CV.

🏷️ Labeling Considerations
Label	Meaning	Details
1	Smishing	Messages designed to deceive, e.g., phishing links, prizes, impersonation
0	Legitimate	Real-world user texts, service messages, medical reminders, etc.

Smishing messages often include:

URGENT actions ("قم الآن", "بسرعة")

Financial deception ("ربحت", "حسابك", "بطاقتك")

Shortened or suspicious URLs

Authority impersonation ("وزارة", "بنك", "شركة الاتصالات")

🧪 Data Preprocessing Expected

Before feeding into the model:

Step	Purpose
Remove diacritics	Normalize script variations
Normalize Arabic letters	Reduce character diversity for consistent tokenization
Tokenize using Farasa	Tokenize Arabic correctly (respecting word roots, clitics)
Pad/truncate sequences	Make input tensors uniform 
Word2Vec embedding	Use either pre-trained or custom-trained embeddings

📦 How to Use It

Place this file in your project at:

Hybrid_Deep_Learning_Smishing/Dataset/smishing_dataset.csv


Then update your data loading code in train.py or similar:

import pandas as pd

df = pd.read_csv("Dataset/smishing_dataset.csv")
texts = df["text"]
labels = df["label"]
